result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
of 10/16/15 Plea and Sentencing hearing held before the Honorable Scott R Needham filed by RPR Vicki Kasten. jll
Original Document Filed in 15CF48

Apprs: CO: SRN, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk: Minot.ADA:   Matthew L Hartung   DF ATTY:  Daniel James Chapman   DF:  David Robert Duarte appeared from jail. Includes 15CF48, 15CF275, 15CT54 and 15CM597. Case called at 1:59 pm. ADA Hartung informs Crt of agreement. Def pleads Guilty to Count one in 15CT54. DE sworn. Crt informs Def of rights. Crt finds Def freely, voluntarily and knowingly makes plea. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds Def guilty of Count one in 15CT54. On motion of the State Crt merges and dismisses Count two.  Based on plea in 15CT54, ADA moves to  amend 15CF48 to OWI 4th within 5 years. Court amends.Def pleads Guilty to amended Count one in 15CF48. DE sworn. Crt informs Def of rights. Crt finds Def freely, voluntarily and knowingly makes plea. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds Def guilty of amended Count one in 15F48. On motion of the State Crt merges and dismisses count four. Counts two and three are dismissed. 15CF275 is dismissed. 15CM597 read in and dismissed for purposes of sentencing. Court waives PSI. Sentencing arguments. Court questions Def. 

On 15CT54 court orders:
2 years probation with conditions w/h
- 60 Days Jail
- F/F $1494.00, Apply Bond
- 24 mo rev, 24 month IID
- AODA Drivers Safety Plan
- $52.00 for blood draw
- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
- Not to enter any business or establishment where the primary purpose is sale of alcohol.
- Any other treatment agent finds appropiate
- DE subject to random UA, PBT or other testing. 
- Court does not order DNA Sample and Surcharge

On 15CF48 Court orders:
3 years probation with conditions w/h
- 1 year jail, good time. Huber for work, seek work and treatment
- Court Costs 1694.00, Apply Bond
- DNA Sample and Surcharge
- $52.00 for blood draw
- 30 month rev, 30 mo IID
- AODA
- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
- Not to enter any business or establishment where the primary purpose is sale of alcohol.
- Any other treatment agent finds appropiate
- DE subject to random UA, PBT or other testing.
- Credit ultimate against ultime sentenced to be determined with the next week

Charges to run concurrent.

-Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.

-Not to enter any business or establishment where the primary purpose is sale of alcohol.

CO: RMW, RPR: Erin Drost, CLERK: E. Ferrill, ADA: Megan E. Kelly,  DF ATTY:  John A. Kucinski,  DF:  David Robert Duarte appeared from jail. Court confirms address.   Court informs def of charges, possible penalties and rights. Def understands.  Waives reading.  NG.  Waives speedy trial. ADA Kelly is requesting $1000.00 CB, Atty Kucinski argues. Court will transfer to SRN.  Status conference scheduled for October 16, 2015 at 02:00 pm.
